---
/**
 * Terms of Use
 *
 * Covers the SignScan iOS app and the ssmit.com website.
 * Reflects the app's actual pricing model: one-time lifetime unlock or a
 * monthly subscription, both sold through Apple.
 */

import SubpageLayout from '@layouts/SubpageLayout.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '@lib/config';

const email = siteConfig.email;
const { priceOwn, priceMonthly } = siteConfig.app;
---

<SubpageLayout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="The terms that govern your use of the SignScan app and ssmit.com — license, purchases, your content, and our responsibilities."
  badge="Legal"
  subtitle="Effective July 19, 2026 · Applies to the SignScan app and ssmit.com"
  illustration="/illustrations/terms-hero.svg"
  illustrationAlt=""
>
  <div class="callout">
    <p>
      <strong>The short version:</strong> SignScan is yours to use for
      anything lawful. Your documents are yours — we claim no rights to them.
      Buy once and the unlock is permanent on your Apple Account; subscribe
      and you can cancel anytime through Apple. The app places your drawn
      signature on documents, but it is not a certified e-signature service —
      for high-stakes agreements, check what your situation requires.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>1. Agreement to these terms</h2>
  <p>
    These Terms of Use are an agreement between you and SSMIT ("we", "us"),
    a software studio based in Sacramento, California. They govern your use
    of the <strong>SignScan</strong> iOS application and the ssmit.com
    website (together, the "Services"). By downloading or using the
    Services, you agree to these terms. If you don't agree, don't use the
    Services.
  </p>
  <p>
    Where you obtained SignScan through Apple's App Store, Apple's standard
    <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/internet-services/itunes/dev/stdeula/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Licensed Application End User License Agreement</a>
    also applies; if it conflicts with these terms, these terms control to
    the extent permitted.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Your license to SignScan</h2>
  <p>
    We grant you a personal, non-exclusive, non-transferable license to use
    SignScan on Apple devices you own or control, as permitted by the App
    Store usage rules. You may not copy, modify, distribute, sell, or lease
    any part of the app, and you may not reverse-engineer it except to the
    extent the law permits despite this restriction.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Purchases, subscriptions, and refunds</h2>
  <p>SignScan's paid tier ("SignScan Pro") is sold through Apple in two forms:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>One-time purchase ({priceOwn}).</strong> A single payment
      permanently unlocks every Pro tool on your Apple Account. It is a
      lifetime license to the software as shipped, not a promise of future
      services.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Monthly subscription ({priceMonthly}/month).</strong>
      Auto-renews monthly through your Apple Account until cancelled.
      Cancel anytime in iOS Settings → Apple Account → Subscriptions, at
      least 24 hours before the current period ends to avoid renewal.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Payment is charged to your Apple Account at confirmation of purchase.
    Prices may vary by region and may change for new purchases; a change
    will never take away a lifetime unlock you already own. Use
    <em>Restore Purchases</em> in the app to recover your unlock on a new
    device. Refunds are handled by Apple under App Store policies — request
    one at <a href="https://reportaproblem.apple.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">reportaproblem.apple.com</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Your content</h2>
  <p>
    Documents you scan, import, sign, or edit are yours. We claim no
    ownership of and no license to your content. Because processing happens
    on your device, we never receive it (see the
    <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>). You are responsible for the
    content you capture and what you do with it — including having the right
    to scan it in the first place.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Signatures — what SignScan is and isn't</h2>
  <p>
    SignScan lets you draw a signature and place it on a document, producing
    a signed PDF. Many everyday agreements accept exactly this. However:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      SignScan is <strong>not</strong> a certified or "qualified" electronic
      signature service and does not provide identity verification, audit
      trails, or cryptographic signing certificates.
    </li>
    <li>
      Whether an electronically signed document is valid for a particular
      purpose depends on the laws and requirements that apply to that
      document. That judgment — and any legal advice about it — is your
      responsibility, not ours.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. Acceptable use</h2>
  <p>You agree not to use the Services to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>violate any law, or scan, alter, or sign documents to deceive or defraud;</li>
    <li>sign another person's name or forge any signature, seal, or stamp;</li>
    <li>fabricate or alter identity documents, currency, or official records;</li>
    <li>infringe anyone's intellectual property or privacy rights.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>7. Accuracy of automated tools</h2>
  <p>
    Text recognition, handwriting reading, translation, table and receipt
    extraction, and similar features are automated and can make mistakes.
    They are provided as conveniences, not certified results — review
    anything important before you rely on it. Redaction and blur permanently
    modify the output copy; keep the original if you need it.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Our intellectual property</h2>
  <p>
    The Services — including the app's code, design, illustrations, icons,
    and the SignScan and SSMIT names — are owned by or licensed to us and
    are protected by intellectual-property laws. These terms give you no
    right to use our branding.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
  <p>
    The Services are provided <strong>"as is" and "as available"</strong>,
    without warranties of any kind, express or implied, including
    merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.
    We do not warrant that the Services will be uninterrupted or error-free.
    Some jurisdictions don't allow certain warranty exclusions, so parts of
    this section may not apply to you.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the maximum extent permitted by law, SSMIT will not be liable for any
    indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or
    for lost profits, data, or goodwill, arising from your use of the
    Services. Our total liability for any claim relating to the Services is
    limited to the amount you paid us for SignScan in the twelve months
    before the claim arose.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Termination</h2>
  <p>
    You can stop using the Services at any time by deleting the app. We may
    suspend or terminate access to the Services for a violation of these
    terms. Sections that by their nature should survive (your content,
    disclaimers, limitation of liability, governing law) survive
    termination.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Changes to these terms</h2>
  <p>
    We may update these terms from time to time; the current version always
    lives at this page with its effective date. Material changes will be
    noted in the app's release notes. Continuing to use the Services after a
    change means you accept the updated terms.
  </p>

  <h2>13. Governing law</h2>
  <p>
    These terms are governed by the laws of the State of California, without
    regard to conflict-of-law rules. Any dispute will be resolved in the
    state or federal courts located in Sacramento County, California, and
    you consent to their jurisdiction.
  </p>

  <h2>14. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    SSMIT · Sacramento, California, USA<br />
    <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a>
  </p>
</SubpageLayout>
